<p style="font-size: 1.1em; margin-top: 20px;">You wake up one morning to find dark clouds gathering above your school.<br />Your friend claims it&rsquo;ll remain sunny because yesterday was bright.<br />Intrigued, you decide to investigate what drives day-to-day changes.<br />Note down the temperature, wind, and humidity throughout the day.<br />By evening, you compare your notes to forecast tomorrow&rsquo;s weather.</p>
<h2 style="color: #663300; background: #fff3cd; padding: 10px; border-left: 8px solid #ffa000; border-radius: 6px;">ğŸ“— Reference</h2>
<p><strong>Grade 7 Social Science &ndash; Chapter 3: Climates of India</strong><br />Topic: Weather vs. Climate</p>
<h2 style="color: #663300; background: #fff3cd; padding: 10px; border-left: 8px solid #ffa000; border-radius: 6px;">ğŸ•µ&zwj;â™€ Scenario: Weather vs. Climate Investigation</h2>
<p>What drives the difference between short-term weather changes and long-term climate patterns?</p>
<p><img src="https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Yaswanth876/InternProject/refs/heads/main/20250625_1136_Weather%20vs.%20Climate%20Cartoon_simple_compose_01jyjv1cevedz8wyz69kpn2v86.png" alt="" /></p>
<h2 style="color: #663300; background: #fff3cd; padding: 10px; border-left: 8px solid #ffa000; border-radius: 6px;">ğŸ§  Logic Used</h2>
<p>Comparison and classification (distinguishing short-term patterns from long-term trends).</p>
<h2 style="color: #663300; background: #fff3cd; padding: 10px; border-left: 8px solid #ffa000; border-radius: 6px;">ğŸ§® Algorithm</h2>
<ol>
<li>List what you observe each hour (rain, sun, wind).</li>
<li>Group observations by day and by season.</li>
<li>Note how values change day-to-day versus month-to-month.</li>
<li>Decide which set describes &ldquo;weather&rdquo; and which describes &ldquo;climate.&rdquo;</li>
</ol>
<h2 style="color: #663300; background: #fff3cd; padding: 10px; border-left: 8px solid #ffa000; border-radius: 6px;">ğŸ§± Block Diagram</h2>
